\subsection{\href{https://beta.lmfdb.org/knowledge/show/hmsurface.component_ideal}{Component ideal}}
\begin{definition*}\label{hmsurface.component_ideal}
\uses{av.polarization,av.princ_polarizable,nf.narrow_class_group}
The adelic Hilbert modular surface may be geometrically reducible, and its components are in bijection with the \hyperref[nf.narrow_class_group]{narrow class group} of the base field $F$. The component corresponding to a given narrow ideal class $[\mathfrak{b}]$ parametrizes abelian surfaces with endomorphism algebra isomorphic to $F$ whose \hyperref[av.polarization]{polarization module} is isomorphic to $\mathbb{Z}_F \oplus \mathfrak{b}$. In particular, the surfaces parametrized are \hyperref[av.princ_polarizable]{principally polarized} if and only if the component ideal is the inverse different of the base field $F$.
\end{definition*}


